insider.com%2F699fc7fc1fb3fcb426487b3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Chinamaxxing%20trend%20is%20going%20viral%20in%20the%20US.%20Chinese%20social%20media%20users%20are%20divided%20over%20what%20it%20means.%3Cp%3EPanuwat%20Dangsungnoen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFrom%20boiled%20apples%20to%20tai%20chi%2C%20Americans%20are%20embracing%20%26quot%3BChinamaxxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChinese%20social%20media%20users%20are%20divided%20over%20what%20it%20means.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20found%20it%20hilarious%20and%20said%20the%20clips%20made%20them%20proud%20to%20be%20Chinese.%20Others%20just%20cringed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Americans%20want%20to%20be%20Chinese%20now.%20China%20isn't%20sure%20how%20to%20feel%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20TikTok%2C%20non-Chinese%20American%20creators%20are%20filming%20themselves%20boiling%20apples%2C%20practicing%20tai%20chi%20at%20sunrise%2C%20and%20drinking%20hot%20water%20%E2%80%94%20all%20soundtracked%20to%20traditional%20Chinese%20instrumentals%20or%20clips%20from%20Mulan.%20They%20call%20it%20%26quot%3BChinamaxxing%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20videos%20are%20pulling%20in%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20self-care%2C%20part%20aesthetic%20role-play%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinamaxxing-tiktok-chinese-habits-wellness-hot-water-boiled-apples-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20trend%3C%2Fa%3E%20taps%20into%20what%20creators%20portray%20as%20a%20calmer%2C%20healthier%20Chinese%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20%26quot%3BChinamaxxing%26quot%3B%20may%20reflect%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20younger%20Americans%20view%20China%2C%20and%20could%20signal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-retail-brands-labubu-luckin-expand-us-open-stores-data-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChinese%20soft%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Chinese%20social%20media%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-app-xiaohongshu-americans-tiktok-ban-help-homework-rednote-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eplatform%20RedNote%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20users%20have%20been%20watching%20closely.%20Their%20reactions%20range%20from%20amused%20pride%20to%20bewilderment%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20outright%20cringe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20happy%20to%20see%20more%20and%20more%20people%20willing%20to%20learn%20about%20Chinese%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20RedNote%20user%20Jiang%20Jiang%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20scrolling%20further%2C%20she%20reconsidered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20videos%20of%20drinking%20hot%20water%20with%20lemon%20slices%20and%20wearing%20red%20clothes%20really%20make%20me%20uncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Btoo%20bizarre.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20Chinese%20person%20eating%20a%20meal%20at%20McDonald's%2C%20wearing%20an%20ugly%20sweater%20for%20Christmas%2C%20and%20then%20announcing%20themselves%20as%20'last%20diagnosed%20American%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20suggested%20parts%20of%20the%20trend%20may%20misrepresent%20Chinese%20traditions%2C%20particularly%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flunar-new-year-traditions-through-the-lens-of-three-photographers-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELunar%20New%20Year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20RedNote%20user%20Jia%20Simin%20wrote%20that%20some%20of%20the%20content%20on%20TikTok%20had%20%26quot%3Bcaused%20dissatisfaction%20among%20Chinese%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECultural%20exchange%20shouldn't%20be%20driven%20by%20%26quot%3Bsuperficial%20imitation%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacob%20Cooke%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Beijing-based%20e-commerce%20consulting%20firm%20WPIC%20Marketing%20%2B%20Technologies%2C%20said%20the%20Chinese%20mostly%20see%20%26quot%3BChinamaxxing%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20positive%20reflection%20of%20Chinese%20culture%20and%20an%20expression%20of%20curiosity%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20negative%20charge%20of%20cultural%20appropriation%20comes%20more%20from%20Chinese%20Americans%20and%20younger%20Chinese%20who%20have%20spent%20time%20abroad.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a1179ab8-57f3-4598-b0bc-cb7c736db9b7%5C%22%3E'I%20suddenly%20feel%20so%20proud'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20cringing.%20Some%20Chinese%20users%20framed%20the%20trend%20as%20a%20cultural%20win%20for%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20RedNote%20user%20who%20goes%20by%20Lie%20Hu%20said%20watching%20the%20%26quot%3Bbizarre%20behavior%26quot%3B%20on%20TikTok%20had%20them%20%26quot%3Blaughing%20like%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20most%20impressive%20cultural%20export%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote%20in%20January.%20%26quot%3BI%20suddenly%20feel%20so%20proud.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20said%20the%20trend%20shows%20non-Chinese%20people%20finally%20seeing%20the%20%26quot%3Bwarmth%20and%20wisdom%20in%20Chinese%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20wisdom%20of%20our%20ancestors%20is%20just%20so%20captivating%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20a%20RedNote%20user%20who%20goes%20by%20CO2.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Chinese%20users%20also%20saw%20the%20trend%20as%20less%20about%20China%20and%20more%20about%20America's%20anxieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20they%20want%20to%20become%20Chinese%20is%20simply%20because%20they%20dislike%20their%20current%20situation%20and%20their%20self-identity%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20one%20RedNote%20user%20who%20goes%20by%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20like%20braised%20food.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20actually%20a%20way%20for%20American%20youth%20to%20express%20their%20extreme%20disappointment%20with%20the%20curre