ting%20and%20incumbent%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20analyst%20Brad%20Zelnick%20in%20a%20note%20to%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20team's%20core%20thesis%20regarding%20Anthropic's%20long-term%20impact%20on%20software%20centers%20around%20the%20argument%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20recent%20focus%20on%20AI%20disruption%2C%20the%20technology%20still%20should%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20substitute%20for%20entire%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVarious%20partnership%20announcements%20earlier%20in%20the%20day%20(including%20Intuit)%20along%20with%20mentioning%20the%20importance%20of%20data%20and%20context%20that%20live%20in%20the%20various%20systems%20of%20record%20and%20engagement%20suggest%20that%20it%20remains%20very%20difficult%20to%20replicate%20or%20displace%20much%20of%20the%20knowledge%2C%20metadata%2C%20and%20workflows%20incumbent%20systems%20have%20amassed%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelnick%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Deutsche%20does%20see%20some%20risk%20for%20software%20stocks%2C%20their%20overall%20view%20on%20the%20industry%20is%20optimistic%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20will%20broadly%20lift%20software%20makers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20view%20is%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20that%20of%20some%20finance%20and%20investing%20pros.%20Renowned%20statistician%20and%20author%20Nassim%20Taleb%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnassim-taleb-ai-disruption-stock-market-software-bankruptcies-black-swan-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecently%20predicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20software%20bankruptcies%20are%20coming%20and%20stock%20gains%20of%20recent%20years%20could%20be%20wiped%20out.%20Yet%2C%20Deutsche%20maintains%20the%20bullish%20view%20that%20the%20market%20has%20room%20for%20both%20software%20and%20AI%20winners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20see%20this%20as%20positive%20for%20the%20infrastructure%2Fcompute%20layer%20given%20the%20increase%20in%20queries%20by%20humans%2Fagents%20against%20underlying%20enterprise%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelnick%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-software-stocks-deutsche-bank-ai-scare-trade-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772044180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6961957964858d02d2181f5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-software-stocks-deutsche-bank-ai-scare-trade-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthropic%20has%20become%20a%20boogeyman%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20with%20Claude's%20capabilities%20slamming%20various%20stock%20sectors.%20Deutsche%20says%20software%20will%20survive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-software-stocks-deutsche-bank-ai-scare-trade-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20happened%20after%20Elon%20Musk%20took%20the%20Russian%20army%20offline%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20computer%20screen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f3a4ce8408f6671803f7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrone%20footage%20gathered%20by%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%20shows%20widespread%20battlefield%20use%20of%20Starlink%20terminals%20by%20Russian%20troops.%3Cp%3EViktor%20Lysenko%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESpaceX%20shut%20down%20Russian%20troops'%20access%20to%20Starlink%20satellite-internet%20terminals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20change%20constrained%20Russian%20military%20capabilities%20and%20created%20opportunities%20for%20Ukrainian%20forces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20days%20following%20the%20shutdown%2C%20Ukraine%20recaptured%20roughly%2077%20square%20miles%20in%20the%20country's%20southeast.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20originally%20ran%20in%20Welt%20and%20appears%20on%20Business%20Insider%20through%20the%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20we've%20got%20left%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Russian%20soldier%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20radios%2C%20cables%20and%20pigeons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decision%20earlier%20this%20month%20by%20SpaceX%20to%20shut%20down%20access%20to%20Starlink%20satellite-internet%20terminals%20caused%20immediate%20chaos%20among%20Russian%20forces%20who%20had%20become%20increasingly%20reliant%20upon%20the%20Elon%20Musk-owned%20company's%20technology%20to%20sustain%20their%20occupation%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20according%20to%20radio%20transmissions%20intercepted%20by%20a%20Ukrainian%20reconnaissance%20unit%20and%20shared%20with%20the%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%2C%20to%20which%20POLITICO%20and%20Business%20Insider%20belong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20communications%20breakdown%20significantly%20constrained%20Russian%20military%20capabilities%2C%20creating%20new%20opportunities%20for%20Ukrainian%20forces.%20In%20the%20days%20following%20the%20shutdown%2C%20Ukraine%20recaptured%20roughly%2077%20square%20miles%20in%20the%20country's%20southeast%2C%20according%20to%20calculations%20by%20the%20news%20agency%20Agence%20France-Presse%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20Washington-based%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20men%20sitting%20at%20brown%20desks%20in%20military%20fatigues%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f3a99e8408f6671803f88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnalysts%20in%20Ukraine's%20Bureviy%20Brigade%20eavesdrop%20on%20Russian%20communications%20from%20an%20underground%20listening%20post%20in%20northeastern%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EViktor%20Lysenko%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20began%20requiring%20verification%20of%20Starlink%20terminals%20on%20Feb.%204%2C%20blocking%20unverified%20Russian%20units%20from%20accessing%20its%20services.%20Almost%20immediately%2C%20Ukrainian%20eavesdroppers%20heard%20Russian%20soldiers%20complaining%20about%20the%20failure%20of%20%26quot%3BKosmos%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BSinka%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20apparently%20code%20names%20for%20Starlink%20satellite%20internet%20and%20the%20messaging%20service%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDamn%20it!%20Looks%20like%20they've%20switched%20off%20all%20the%20Starlinks%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Russian%20soldier%20exclaimed.%20%26quot%3BThe%20connection%20is%20gone%2C%20completely%20gone.%20The%20images%20aren't%20being%20transmitted%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20shouted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20the%20recordings%20were%20played%20for%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporter%20Network%20reporters%20in%20an%20underground%20listening%20post%20maintained%20by%20the%20Bureviy%20Brigade%20in%20northeastern%20Ukraine.%20Neither%20SpaceX%20nor%20the%20Russian%20Foreign%20Ministry%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20Russian%20side%2C%20we%20observed%20on%20the%20very%20day%20Starlink%20was%20shut%20down%20that%20artillery%20and%20mortar%20fire%20dropped%20drastically.%20Drone%20drops%20and%20FPV%20attacks%20also%20suddenly%20decreased%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20Ukrainian%20aerial%20reconnaissance%20operator%20from%20the%20Bureviy%20Brigade%20who%20would%20agree%20to%20be%20identified%20only%20by%20the%20call%20sign%20Mustang%2C%20referring%20to%20first-person%20view%20drones.%20%26quot%3BCoordination%20between%20their%20units%20has%20also%20become%20more%20difficult%20since%20then.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20satellite%20internet%20network%20has%20become%20a%20crucial%20tool%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20sustaining%20high-tech%20drone%20operations%20and%20replacing%20walkie-talkies%20in%20low-tech%20combat.%20Since%20Russia's%20February%202022%20invasion%2C%20which%20destroyed%20much%20of%20Ukraine's%20traditional%20communications%20infrastructure%2C%20Western%20governments%20have%20provided%20thousands%20of%20the%20Starlink%20units%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20military%20fatigues%20with%20a%20Ukrainian%20flag%20on%20his%20shoulder.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f3ae2e8408f6671803f92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20Russians%20had%20more%20devices%20than%20we%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20identified%20by%20the%20call%20sign%20Mustang%3Cp%3EViktor%20Lysenko%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Walkie%20talkies%20under%20red%20light%20on%20a%20shelf%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f3b0450f42603b0f8e3ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EViktor%20Lysenko%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20portable%20terminals%2C%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20lay%20kilometers%20of%20cable%20that%20can%20be%20damaged%20by%20shelling%20or%20drone%20strikes.%20Drone%20footage%20can%20be%20transmitted%20in%20real%20time%20to%20command%20posts%2C%20artillery%20and%20mortar%20fire%20can%20be%20corrected%20with%20precision%2C%20and%20operational%20information%20can%20be%20shared%20instantly%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20apps%20such%20as%20Signal%20or%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%20of%20the%20Russian%20invasion%2C%20Starlink%20access%20gave%20Ukraine's%20defenders%20a%20decisive%20operational%20advantage.%20Those%20in%20besieged%20Mariupol%20sent%20signs%20of%20life%20in%20spring%202022%20via%20the%20backpack-size%20white%20dishes%2C%20and%20army%20units%20used%20them%20to%20coordinate%20during%20brutal%20house-to-house%20fighting%20in%20Bakhmut%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellite%20internet%20became%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%2C%20if%20not%20the%20most%20important%20components%26quot%3B%20of%20Ukraine's%20way%20of%20war%2C%20according%20to%20military%20analyst%20Franz-Stefan%20Gady%2C%20an%20adviser%20to%20European%20governments%20and%20security%20agencies%20who%20regularly%20visits%20Ukrainian%20units.%20%26quot%3BStarlink%20constituted%20the%20backbone%20of%20connectivity%20that%20enabled%20accelerated%20kill%20chains%20by%20helping%20create%20a%20semi-transparent%20battlefield.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20operational%20advantages%20of%20Starlink%20did%20not%20go%20unnoticed%20by%20Russian%20forces.%20By%20the%20third%20year%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Starlink%20terminals%20were%20increasingly%20turning%20up%20in%20Russian-occupied%20territory.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20documented%20cases%20surfaced%20in%20January%202024%20in%20the%20Serebryansky%20forest.%20Month%20by%20month%2C%20Ukrainian%20reconnaissance%20drones%20spotted%20more%20of%20the%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20government%20subsequently%20contacted%20Musk's%20company%2C%20urging%20it%20to%20block%20Russian%20access%20to%20the%20network.%20Mykhailo%20Fedorov%2C%20then%20digital%20minister%20and%20now%20defense%20minister%2C%20alleged%20Russian%20forces%20were%20acquiring%20the%20devices%20via%20third%20countries.%20%26quot%3BUkraine%20will%20continue%20using%20Starlink%2C%20and%20Russian%20use%20will%20be%20restricted%20to%20the%20maximum%20extent%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Fedorov%20pledged%20in%20spring%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Russian%20use%20of%20the%20terminals%20continued%20to%20grow%20throughout%202025%2C%20and%20their%20use%20was%20not%20limited%20to%20artillery%20or%20drone%20units.%20Even%20Russian%20infantry%20soldiers%20were%20carrying%20mini%20Starlink%20terminals%20in%20their%20backpacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20found%20Starlink%20terminals%20at%20virtually%20every%20Russian%20position%20along%20the%20contact%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mustang.%20%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20Russians%20had%20more%20devices%20than%20we%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20listening%20post%20this%20month%2C%20he%20scrolled%20through%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20images%20from%20late%202025%20showing%20Russian%20Starlink%20terminals%20set%20up%20between%20trees%20or%20beside%20the%20entrances%20to%20their%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20targeted%20their%20positions%20deliberately%2C%26quot%3B%20Mustang%20continued.%20%26quot%3BBut%20even%20if%20we%20destroyed%20a%20terminal%20in%20the%20morning%20or%20evening%2C%20a%20new%20one%20was%20already%20installed%20by%20the%20next%20morning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Russian-occupied%20eastern%20Ukrainian%20city%20of%20Kreminna%2C%20there%20was%20even%20a%20shop%20where%20soldiers%20could%20buy%20Starlink%20terminals%20starting%20in%202024.%20According%20to%20Ukrainian%20officials%2C%20these%20devices%20were%20not%20registered%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20move%20in%20early%20February%20to%20enforce%20a%20stricter%20verification%20system%20effectively%20cut%20off%20unregistered%20Starlink%20terminals%20operating%20in%20Russian-occupied%20areas.%20Only%20devices%20approved%20and%20placed%20on%20a%20Ukrainian%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20%26quot%3Bwhitelist%26quot%3B%20remained%20active%2C%20while%20terminals%20used%20by%20Russian%20forces%20were%20remotely%20deactivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20it%2C%20basically%20no%20one%20has%20internet%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Russian%20soldier%20said%20in%20one%20of%20the%20messages%20played%20for%20Axel%20Springer%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BEverything's%20off%2C%20everything's%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20temporary%20shutdown%20allowed%20Ukraine%20to%20slow%20the%20momentum%20of%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20forces%2C%20although%20the%20localized%20counteroffensives%20do%20not%20represent%20a%20fundamental%20shift%20along%20the%20front.%20Soldiers%20from%20other%20Ukrainian%20units%2C%20including%20the%20Black%20Arrow%20battalion%2C%20confirmed%20the%20military%20consequences%20of%20the%20Starlink%20outage%20for%20Russian%20forces%20in%20their%20sectors%20in%20interviews%20with%20the%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20mid-February%2C%20Russian%20shelling%20had%20increased%20again%2C%20though%20largely%20against%20frontline%20positions%20that%20had%20long%20been%20identified%20and%20precisely%20mapped%20%E2%80%94%20suggesting%20that%20Russia%20has%20yet%20to%20fully%20restore%20all%20of%20its%20lost%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20analysts%20from%20the%20Bureviy%20Brigade%20say%20Russian%20forces%20are%20scrambling%20for%20alternatives.%20They%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20rely%20far%20more%20heavily%20on%20radio%20communication%2C%20according%20to%20Mustang%2C%20which%20creates%20additional%20opportunities%20for%20interception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20units%20will%20likely%20attempt%20to%20switch%20to%20their%20own%20satellite%20terminals.%20But%20their%20speed%20and%20connection%20quality%20are%20significantly%20lower%2C%20Mustang%20says.%20And%20because%20of%20their%20size%2C%20the%20devices%20are%20difficult%20to%20conceal.%26quot%3BThe%20shutdown%20of%20Starlink%2C%20even%20if%20only%20of%20limited%20effect%20for%20now%2C%20highlights%20the%20limited%20ability%20of%20the%20Russian%20armed%20forces%20to%20rapidly%20implement%20ongoing%20cycles%20of%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Col.%20Markus%20Reisner%20of%20the%20Austrian%20Armed%20Forces.%20%26quot%3BThis%20could%20represent%20a%20potential%20point%20of%20leverage%20for%20Western%20supporters%20to%20provide%20swift%20and%20sustainable%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20at%20this%20stage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIbrahim%20Naber%20is%20a%20chief%20reporter%20at%20Welt.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-russian-army-offline-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772043875000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f3bc050f42603b0f8e403%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-russian-army-offline-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20SpaceX%20decided%20to%20shut%20down%20access%20to%20Starlink%20satellite-internet%20terminals%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20it%20caused%20immediate%20chaos%20among%20Russian%20forces.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Insider%20Inc.)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-russian-army-offline-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20to%20Coral%20Gables%20for%20my%20dogs.%20I'm%20spending%20almost%20%242%2C000%20more%20in%20rent%2C%20but%20we%20get%20to%20walk%20everywhere.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20posing%20with%20two%20French%20Bulldogs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F698cc6a2e1ba468a96abdceb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20moved%20to%20a%20more%20expensive%20neighborhood%20in%20Miami%20for%20her%20dogs.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20chose%20a%20more%20expensive%20neighborhood%20because%20it's%20dog-friendly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20pay%20%244%2C700%20a%20month%20in%20rent%20to%20prioritize%20my%20dogs'%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoving%20to%20a%20different%20ZIP%20code%20gave%20us%20a%20more%20walkable%2C%20community-centered%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20that%20th