0frustrated%20users%20to%20disconnect%20alarms%20and%20may%20forget%20to%20restore%20power%20%E2%80%94%20a%20risk%20that's%20especially%20relevant%20with%20this%20model%20because%20it%20was%20the%20most%20sensitive%20to%20aerosol%20smoke%20in%20my%20testing.%20While%20I%20didn't%20experience%20any%20nuisance%20alarms%20when%20following%20my%20local%20code%20requirements%20for%20placement%2C%20improper%20placement%20too%20close%20to%20stoves%20or%20bathrooms%20could%20lead%20to%20frequent%20false%20alarms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223134%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20First%20Alert%20500V%20sitting%20outside%20its%20box%20on%20a%20white%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f0ce650f42603b0f8ddcf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20experts%20recommend%20hardwired%20detectors%2C%20smoke%20alarms%20with%20replaceable%20batteries%20are%20better%20than%20those%20with%2010-year%20sealed%20batteries.%3Cp%3EJanelle%20Leeson%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20clear%20voice%20alerts%20and%20effective%20alarms%20gave%20me%20confidence%20that%20this%20would%20wake%20my%20family.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20alarm%20is%20loud%20and%20attention-grabbing%20%E2%80%94%20comparable%20to%20my%20best%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20pick%20and%20noticeably%20louder%20than%20our%20budget%20and%20smart%20picks.%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20volume%20%E2%80%94%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%20sounds%20urgent%20too.%20The%20beep%20sounds%20more%20like%20an%20emergency%20broadcast%20system%20than%20a%20typical%20smoke%20alarm%2C%20which%20sets%20it%20apart%20from%20non-urgent%20alarms.%20Once%20programmed%2C%20it%20announces%20the%20specific%20location%3A%20%26quot%3BWarning%2C%20evacuate%2C%20smoke%20in%20%5Broom%20name%5D%2C%20evacuate.%26quot%3B%20After%20silencing%20during%20testing%2C%20it%20announces%20%26quot%3Balarm%20has%20been%20silenced%26quot%3B%20and%20continues%20flashing%20a%20red%20light%20as%20a%20visual%20reminder%20until%20the%20smoke%20clears.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHowever%2C%20it%20has%20a%20photoelectric%20sensor%20only%20and%20limited%20interconnectivity%20compatibility.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20alarm%20uses%20photoelectric%20detection%20only%2C%20which%20may%20be%20slower%20to%20detect%20fast-flaming%20fires.%20While%20it%20connects%20to%20other%20compatible%20First%20Alert%20units%2C%20compatibility%20is%20limited%2C%20with%20First%20Alert%20SM500V%20being%20the%20only%20option%20for%20a%20wireless%2C%20battery-powered%20interconnected%20safety%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20prefer%20a%20sealed%2010-year%20battery%20unit%2C%20I%20recommend%20the%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15118141709mv-20%26h%3D746dd40e0ce01e6e64b22a3b742a4f61a16dafb28dbb05d093f3dba1fe816e33%26postID%3D699de7aa08fe9c5b3d37655d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-smoke-detectors%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSM310-10-Year-Sealed-Battery-Sensor%252Fdp%252FB0CLVV1R8Z%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFirst%20Alert%20SM310%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20also%20performed%20well%20in%20testing%20and%20has%20the%20advantage%20of%20dual%20sensors%2C%20but%20does%20not%20have%20interconnectivity%20compatibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2244514f0d-9a2c-4325-bd2b-9eca7aded2fc%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20to%20look%20for%5C%22%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20the%20best%20smoke%20detectors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20shopping%20for%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%2C%20it's%20critical%20not%20to%20skimp%20on%20the%20most%20important%20features.%20%26quot%3BWe%20estimate%20that%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20you%20had%20about%2017%20minutes%20to%20escape%20from%20a%20home%20fire%20while%20today%20that%20time%20could%20be%20just%20three%20minutes%20or%20less%20from%20the%20time%20the%20fire%20starts%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20says.%20This%20dramatic%20reduction%20is%20due%20to%20the%20more%20synthetic%20materials%20in%20our%20homes%20and%20changes%20in%20how%20we%20build%20them.%20%26quot%3BWall%20linings%2C%20windows%20and%20interior%20doors%20fail%20more%20quickly.%20Floors%20collapse%20more%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20For%20the%20best%20protection%20against%20today's%20faster-burning%20fires%2C%20consider%20these%20features%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECertifications%20and%20safety%20standards%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20UL%20Standard%20217%2C%208th%20Edition%20or%20later%20is%20the%20current%20safety%20standard%20for%20smoke%20alarms%20and%20should%20be%20clearly%20marked%20on%20the%20detector%20packaging%2C%20on%20the%20alarm%20itself%2C%20and%20in%20the%20instruction%20manual.%20%26quot%3BUL%20certification%20means%20the%20product%20has%20been%20independently%20tested%20and%20verified%20to%20perform%20as%20the%20manufacturer%20claims%20under%20specific%20conditions.%20Unlisted%20or%20improperly%20certified%20products%20may%20fail%20to%20detect%20smoke%2C%20respond%20too%20slowly%2C%20or%20malfunction%20altogether%2C%26quot%3B%20Sayles%20says.%20Building%20codes%20generally%20require%20smoke%20detectors%20to%20be%20certified%20by%20a%20nationally%20recognized%20testing%20laboratory%2C%20such%20as%20UL%20(Underwriters%20Laboratories)%20or%20ETL%20(Intertek).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20my%20research%2C%20I%20am%20currently%20not%20recommending%20smoke%20detectors%20from%20Kidde%2C%20Siterwell%2C%20or%20X-sense%2C%20as%20I've%20found%20a%20record%20of%20defective%20products%2C%20recalls%2C%20and%2For%20lapses%20in%20safety%20certification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESensor%20type%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20best%20smoke%20detector%20uses%20ionization%20and%20photoelectric%20sensors.%20Ionization%20sensors%20respond%20faster%20to%20fast-flaming%20fires%2C%20like%20a%20grease%20fire%20on%20the%20stove%20or%20burning%20newspaper%2C%20which%20produce%20intense%20heat%20and%20flames%20but%20relatively%20little%20smoke.%20Photoelectric%20sensors%20are%20more%20responsive%20to%20smoldering%20fires%2C%20like%20an%20ember%20catching%20a%20curtain%20or%20an%20electrical%20fault%2C%20which%20produce%20large%20amounts%20of%20smoke%20before%20ever%20creating%20a%20flame.%20%26quot%3BYou%20cannot%20predict%20the%20type%20of%20fire%20you%20may%20have%20or%20when%20it%20will%20occur%2C%26quot%3B%20McKelvey%20As%20a%20result%2C%20NFPA%20recommends%20buying%20combination%20smoke%20alarms%2C%20which%20feature%20both%20ionization%20and%20photoelectric%20technologies%20in%20a%20single%20device%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPower%20source%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20smoke%20detector%20for%20a%20home%20is%20hardwired%20with%20battery%20backup.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BWorking%20batteries%20are%20essential%20for%20these%20alarms%20because%20they%20ensure%20that%20the%20smoke%20alarms%20will%20operate%20in%20a%20fire%20even%20if%20the%20home%20loses%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20McKelvey%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20battery-only%20is%20your%20only%20option%2C%20Sayles%20recommends%20replaceable%20battery%20units%20over%20sealed%2010-year%20units.%20While%20sealed%20batteries%20may%20seem%20convenient%2C%20they%20can%20fail%20unpredictably.%20Smoke%20detectors%20have%20manufacturing%20dates%2C%20but%20most%20homeowners%20either%20can't%20or%20don't%20check%20them%20at%20the%20time%20of%20purchase.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20know%20how%20long%20that%20alarm%20sat%20on%20a%20shelf%20before%20purchase.%20If%20the%20battery%20fails%20early%2C%20the%20entire%20unit%20becomes%20useless%2C%26quot%3B%20Sayles%20explains.%20Replaceable%20batteries%20allow%20you%20to%20correct%20a%20failure%20immediately%20rather%20than%20replacing%20the%20whole%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterconnectivity%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20smoke%20detector%20communicates%20with%20other%20alarms%20throughout%20your%20home.%20%26quot%3BInterconnected%20smoke%20alarms%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20wireless%20or%20hard-wired%20%E2%80%94%20are%20designed%20so%20that%20when%20one%20alarm%20sounds%2C%20they%20all%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20McKelvey%20says.%20Sayles%20says%20that%20this%20feature%20significantly%20improves%20early%20warning%20and%20escape%20time%20by%20giving%20everyone%20in%20the%20house%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20are%20%E2%80%94%20critical%20extra%20seconds%20to%20escape.%20This%20is%20a%20life-saving%20advantage%20in%20multi-story%20homes%20or%20layouts%20where%20bedrooms%20are%20far%20from%20main%20living%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20latching%20indicator%20continues%20to%20flash%20a%20red%20LED%20light%20even%20after%20an%20alarm%20is%20silenced%2C%20identifying%20the%20exact%20origin%20of%20the%20alert%20for%20both%20homeowners%20and%20first%20responders.%20This%20is%20critical%20in%20an%20interconnected%20system%20where%20multiple%20alarms%20are%20sounding%2C%20and%20all%20the%20interconnected%20alarms%20I%20recommend%20in%20this%20guide%20include%20this%20feature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccessibility%20and%20alert%20features%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BStrobe%20lights%2C%20low-frequency%20alarms%2C%20and%20interconnected%20systems%20are%20critical%20for%20residents%20with%20hearing%20impairments.%20For%20older%20adults%20or%20those%20with%20limited%20mobility%2C%20early%20detection%20is%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20alarms%20must%20activate%20quickly%20and%20throughout%20the%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Sayles%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20prioritized%20alarms%20with%20voice%20alerts%20that%20specify%20alarm%20type%20and%20location%2C%20instant%20remote%20smartphone%20notifications%20for%20accessibility%2C%20and%20decibel%20ratings%20high%20enough%20to%20wake%20heavy%20sleepers.%20While%20we%20tested%20two%20alarms%20with%20low-frequency%20alerts%20specifically%20designed%20for%20people%20who%20are%20hard%20of%20hearing%2C%20they%20didn't%20make%20our%20final%20recommendations%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20features%20or%20design%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NFPA%20standards%2C%20smoke%20alarms%20must%20measure%20at%20least%2085%20decibels%20at%2010%20feet%20to%20meet%20code%20requirements.%20You%20can%20verify%20a%20model's%20decibel%20rating%20on%20the%20product%20page%20or%20in%20its%20manual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMultifunctionality%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECombination%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20detectors%20can%20be%20effective%2C%20but%20according%20to%20Sayles%2C%20they%20can%20also%20cause%20confusion.%20%26quot%3BDifferent%20beep%20patterns%2C%20lights%2C%20and%20alerts%20can%20be%20misinterpreted%20by%20homeowners%2C%20especially%20years%20after%20installation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20To%20help%20users%20avoid%20confusion%2C%20the%20combination%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20detectors%20I've%20recommended%20in%20this%20guide%20all%20feature%20voice%20alerts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstallation%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHardwired%20units%20require%20basic%20electrical%20knowledge%2C%20including%20shutting%20off%20power%20at%20the%20breaker%20and%20testing%20wires%20with%20a%20voltage%20tester%20before%20connecting%20the%20unit's%20wiring.%20Battery-powered%20detectors%20don't%20require%20any%20electrical%20work%20but%20still%20need%20to%20be%20securely%20mounted%20to%20walls%20or%20ceilings%2C%20often%20using%20drywall%20anchors.%20For%20our%20testing%2C%20we%20prioritized%20models%20that%20included%20all%20necessary%20mounting%20hardware%20and%20clear%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20local%20fire%20departments%20offer%20free%20smoke%20alarm%20installation%20and%20inspection%20services.%20You%20can%20contact%20your%20local%20fire%20department%20to%20ask%20about%20available%20programs%20in%20your%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaintenance%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%20a%20minimum%2C%20all%20smoke%20detectors%20should%20have%20an%20easily%20accessible%20test%20button%2C%20and%20battery-powered%20models%20should%20clearly%20indicate%20when%20batteries%20are%20low%2C%20whether%20through%20a%20chirping%20sound%2C%20flashing%20light%2C%20or%20both.%20Smoke%20detectors%20should%20be%20cleaned%20of%20dust%20with%20a%20vacuum%20or%20compressed%20air%20spray%20once%20a%20month%2C%20tested%20when%20first%20installed%20and%20twice%20a%20year%20thereafter%20using%20both%20the%20test%20button%20and%20aerosol%20smoke%2C%20and%20batteries%20should%20be%20replaced%20as%20needed%20(typically%20every%206%20months%20to%202%20years%20depending%20on%20battery%20type).%20The%20entire%20unit%20should%20be%20replaced%20every%2010%20years%2C%20or%20sooner%20if%20a%20sealed%20battery%20dies%20or%20if%20the%20alarm%20fails%20to%20activate%20during%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3bc0727-e084-49bb-b6bf-674fad409190%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20we%20test%5C%22%3EHow%20we%20test%20the%20best%20smoke%20detectors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20checks%20the%20voltage%20of%20a%20smoke%20detector%20in%20her%20ceiling.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699e245850f42603b0f8d647%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20tested%20a%20dozen%20smoke%20alarms%20in%20my%20own%20home%20for%20ease%20of%20installation%2C%20accuracy%2C%20and%20reliability.%3Cp%3EJanelle%20Leeson%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20insights%20from%20fire%20safety%20experts%20to%20develop%20an%20objective%20testing%20methodology%20with%20a%20point-scoring%20system%20to%20rank%20each%20of%20the%209%20smoke%20detectors.%20I%20also%20circled%20back%20to%20Sayles%20with%20questions%20about%20my%20aerosol%20smoke%20testing%20methodology%20and%20outcomes%20to%20ensure%20my%20approach%20and%20conclusions%20were%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECertifications%20and%20safety%20standards%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Before%20I%20began%20hands-on%20testing%2C%20I%20verified%20that%20each%20smoke%20detector%20featured%20clear%20certification%20markings%20from%20recognized%20testing%20laboratories%20such%20as%20UL%20or%20ETL.%20I%20checked%20device%20packaging%2C%20the%20device%20itself%2C%20and%20instruction%20manuals%20for%20certifications%20and%20safety%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEase%20of%20installation%20and%20setup%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20timed%20how%20long%20each%20detector%20took%20to%20install%20and%20noted%20whether%20instructions%20were%20clear%2C%20if%20all%20mounting%20hardware%20was%20included%2C%20and%20whether%20additional%20tools%20were%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlarm%20reliability%20(smoke%20detection)%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20each%20detector%2C%20I%20used%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15118141709mv-20%26h%3D1603cb5c0fc056a4e2b6a1706ec8d4676fc3891cc421cf459d5751bc06c3af9c%26postID%3D699de7aa08fe9c5b3d37655d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-smoke-detectors%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FCRC-2105-Liquid-Detector-Aerosol%252Fdp%252FB001B3BL0S%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECRC%20Aerosol%20Smoke%20Test%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20a%20consistent%20protocol%3A%20I%20applied%20two%20three-second%20bursts%20of%20aerosol%20smoke%20directed%20toward%20the%20detector%2C%20with%20approximately%20two%20seconds%20between%20sprays.%20I%20began%20testing%20at%20a%20distance%20of%2036%20inches%20and%20progressively%20moved%20closer%20%E2%80%94%20to%2024%20inches%2C%2012%20inches%2C%206%20inches%2C%20and%20finally%203%20inches%20%E2%80%94%20until%20the%20alarm%20activated.%20I%20waited%20at%20least%2010%20seconds%20between%20distances%20to%20allow%20the%20smoke%20to%20disperse%20and%20reach%20the%20sensor.%20This%20test%20was%20repeated%20a%20minimum%20of%20three%20times%20per%20detector%2C%20with%20up%20to%2012%20hours%20between%20test%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20each%20trial%2C%20I%20recorded%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDistance%20at%20which%20the%20alarm%20activated%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETime%20from%20first%20spray%20to%20alarm%20activation%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EConsistency%20of%20activation%20across%20all%20three%20trials%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhether%20the%20hush%2Fsilence%20feature%20worked%20effectively%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDetectors%20that%20consistently%20activated%20at%20greater%20distances%20across%20multiple%20trials%20scored%20highest.%20Any%20detector%20that%20failed%20to%20activate%20by%203%20inches%20across%20all%20trials%20was%20disqualified%20from%20further%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20holds%20sprays%20an%20aerosol%20can%20towards%20a%20battery-powered%20smoke%20detector.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699e23a6e8408f66718031cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20talked%20to%20experts%20and%20put%20smoke%20detectors%20through%20rigorous%20tests%20in%20my%20own%20home%20to%20make%20my%20picks%20for%20this%20guide.%3Cp%3EJanelle%20Leeson%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlarm%20volume%20and%20clarity%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20triggered%20each%20alarm%20and%20measured%20the%20decibel%20level%20using%20a%20sound%20meter%20application%20on%20my%20phone.%20I%20also%20evaluated%20the%20perceived%20urgency%20of%20the%20tone%20and%20clarity%20of%20voice%20alerts%20from%20inside%20the%20room%2C%20outside%20the%20room%2C%20and%20one%20floor%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccessibility%20features%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20scored%20each%20detector%20based%20on%20the%20number%20of%20accessibility%20features%20it%20included%2C%20such%20as%20voice%20alerts%2C%20low-frequency%20alarms%2C%20visual%20strobe%20lights%2C%20and%20smartphone%20notifications.%20For%20detectors%20with%20those%20features%2C%20I%20then%20assessed%20their%20functionality.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20evaluated%20whether%20voice%20instructions%20were%20location-specific%20and%20easy%20to%20understand%2C%20and%20observed%20visual%20indicators%20during%20both%20alarm%20and%20non-alarm%20states%2C%20noting%20brightness%20and%20visibility%20in%20daylight%20and%20low%20light%20from%20different%20angles.%20Detectors%20with%20more%20accessibility%20features%20scored%20the%20highest%20in%20my%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESensitivity%20and%20false%20alarm%20resistance%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20According%20to%20Sanders%2C%20nuisance%20alarms%20or%20false%20alarms%20are%20most%20often%20related%20to%20cooking%20or%20bathroom%20steam.%20To%20evaluate%20false%20alarm%20resistance%2C%20I%20followed%20my%20local%20fire%20code%20requirements%20for%20smoke%20alarm%20placement%20and%20conducted%20two%20key%20tests%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteam%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Portland%20codes%20recommend%20that%20detectors%20not%20be%20placed%20within%203%20feet%20of%20a%20bathroom%2C%20so%20I%20ran%20a%20hot%20shower%20with%20the%20bathroom%20door%20open%20and%20placed%20each%20detector%204%20feet%20from%20the%20door.%20I%20monitored%20for%20activation%20over%20a%205-minute%20period.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECooking%20vapor%20test%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Portland%20code%20requires%20detectors%20to%20be%20no%20less%20than%2010%20feet%20from%20a%20cooking%20device%20but%20no%20more%20than%2020%20feet%2C%20so%20I%20boiled%20water%20on%20the%20stove%20with%20each%20detector%20placed%2012%20feet%20away.%20I%20monitored%20for%20activation%20over%20a%205-minute%20period.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterconnectivity%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20triggered%20one%20alarm%20in%20each%20interconnected%20system%20and%20verified%20whether%20all%20connected%20units%20activated%2C%20measuring%20any%20delay%20between%20alarms.%20For%20detectors%20with%20location-specific%20voice%20alerts%2C%20I%20confirmed%20whether%20voice%20alerts%20correctly%20identified%20the%20originating%20room.%20I%20also%20tested%20whether%20silencing%20one%20unit%20silenced%20all%20interconnected%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaintenance%20and%20testing%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20evaluated%20how%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20manually%20test%20each%20alarm%20using%20the%20test%20button%2C%20clean%20vents%20or%20sensors%20per%20manufacturer%20instructions%2C%20identify%20the%20manufacturing%20date%20and%20expiration%20information%2C%20and%20replace%20batteries%20when%20applicable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e9b72006-c35e-431c-bf7f-9a8f4981795a%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22FAQs%5C%22%3EBest%20smoke%20detector%20FAQs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3EWhy%20do%20we%20only%20recommend%20First%20Alert%20smoke%20detectors%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EI%20researched%20and%20tested%20smoke%20detectors%20from%20multiple%20brands%2C%20but%20First%20Alert%20consistently%20outperformed%20the%20competition%20across%20my%20testing%20criteria.%20Some%20brands%20didn't%20make%20it%20past%20the%20research%20phase%20due%20to%20a%20history%20of%20defective%20products%2C%20recalls%2C%20or%20lapses%20in%20safety%20certification.%20Others%20failed%20to%20pass%20or%20were%20significantly%20outperformed%20by%20First%20Alert%20models%20in%20hands-on%20testing%20for%20effectiveness%2C%20durability%2C%20features%2C%20and%20overall%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EShould%20my%20smoke%20detector%20have%20a%20CO%20detector%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ECombination%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20detectors%20offer%20important%20protection%2C%20as%20carbon%20monoxide%20is%20a%20deadly%2C%20odorless%2C%20and%20colorless%20gas.%20However%2C%20Sayles%20says%20combination%20units%20can%20cause%20confusion%20if%20alerts%20for%20carbon%20monoxide%20and%20smoke%20are%20not%20clearly%20and%20easily%20distinguished%20from%20each%20other.%20My%20pick%20for%20the%20best%20combination%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20detector%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15118141709mv-20%26h%3Def2029b0a44ff958dcf2c5e5ca10715f93f05911e28295eafd8a10378b8811db%26postID%3D699de7aa08fe9c5b3d37655d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-smoke-detectors%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSMCO100V-AC-Interconnect-Hardwire-Combination-Monoxide%252Fdp%252FB0CV553YL4%252F%253Fth%253D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFirst%20Alert%20SMCO100V-AC%20Interconnect%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20features%20voice%20alerts%20that%20clearly%20distinguish%20between%20smoke%20and%20carbon%20monoxide%20alerts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%20for%20people%20who%20are%20hard%20of%20hearing%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nfpa.org%2Feducation-and-research%2Fresearch%2Ffire-protection-research-foundation%2Fprojects-and-reports%2Faudible-alarm-signal-waking-effectiveness-literature-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENFPA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20smoke%20detectors%20with%20low-frequency%20alarms%20at%20520%20Hz%20are%20most%20effective%20in%20waking%20individuals%20who%20are%20hard%20of%20hearing.%20While%20we%20tested%20two%20alarms%20with%20low-frequency%20features%2C%20neither%20met%20our%20overall%20quality%20and%20performance%20standards%20for%20recommendation.%20I%20recommend%20the%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15118141709mv-20%26h%3D54fc95f94949fbc3c2041683721086b0be57caa830cbeb9d9b80b7b48a8c2310%26postID%3D699de7aa08fe9c5b3d37655d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-smoke-detectors%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FFirst-Alert-Hardwire-Monoxide-SMCO600NV-AC%252Fdp%252FB0DS2VG4P1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFirst%20Alert%20SC5%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20most%20accessible%20option%20in%20our%20roundup.%20Its%20smartphone%20and%20email%20notifications%20provide%20visual%20alerts%20that%20can%20supplement%20auditory%20alarms.%20For%20help%20identifying%20specialized%20low-frequency%20smoke%20alarms%20or%20alerting%20devices%20for%20your%20specific%20needs%2C%20contact%20your%20local%20fire%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%20for%20a%20house%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESayles%20recommends%20hardwired%2C%20dual-sensor%20alarms%20with%20replaceable%20batteries%20and%20interconnect%20capabilities.%20Our%20best%20overall%20pick%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15118141709mv-20%26h%3D5a2548613c663d6aa0ef31867d96452932c16b5e70c7683d200b4401949b8ec7%26postID%3D699de7aa08fe9c5b3d37655d%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fhome%252Fbest-smoke-detectors%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FFirst-Alert-SM300-AC-Interconnect-Hardwire%252Fdp%252FB0F6ZMRB4K%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFirst%20Alert%20SM300-AC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20combines%20all%20of%20Sayles'%20recommended%20features%20%E2%80%94%20hardwired%20power%20with%20battery%20backup%2C%20dual%20sensors%2C%20and%20interconnect%20capability%20%E2%80%94%20making%20it%20the%20most%20comprehensive%20safety%20solution%20for%20most%20homes.%20However%2C%20even%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%20with%20the%20most%20advanced%20safety%20features%20will%20not%20protect%20you%20in%20an%20emergency%20if%20it%20is%20not%20properly%20installed%2C%20maintained%2C%20and%20replaced%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDo%20smoke%20detectors%20need%20to%20be%20cleaned%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20use%20compressed%20air%20or%20a%20vacuum%20to%20remove%20dust%20from%20smoke%20detectors%20monthly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAre%20hardwired%20or%20battery%20smoke%20detectors%20better%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EHardwired%20smoke%20detectors%20with%20replaceable%20battery%20backup%20are%20the%20gold%20standard%2C%20according%20to%20Sayles.%20This%20combination%20ensures%20your%20alarm%20will%20never%20be%20without%20power%2C%20and%20the%20batteries%20can%20be%20replaced%20without%20tossing%20the%20entire%20unit%20before%20its%2010-year%20lifespan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20best%20smoke%20detector%20for%20a%20kitchen%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20smoke%20detectors%20are%20suitable%20for%20the%20kitchen%2C%20as%20proper%20placement%20is%20the%20single%20most%20important%20factor%20in%20preventing%20false%20alarms.%20%26quot%3BSmoke%20alarms%20should%20be%20installed%20at%20least%2010%20feet%20away%20from%20cooking%20appliances%20to%20help%20prevent%20those%20alarms%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20says.%20However%2C%20if%20your%20smoke%20detector%20is%20nearing%20its%2010-year%20replacement%20date%20and%20you've%20struggled%20with%20frequent%20nuisance%20alarms%20despite%20proper%20placement%2C%20newer%2C%20dual-sensor%20technology%20may%20help.%20%26quot%3BNew%20technology%20can%20better%20distinguish%20between%20smoke%20from%20a%20fire%20and%20steam%20from%20cooking.%20It%20may%20be%20worth%20investing%20in%20these%20new%20smoke%20alarms%20to%20ensure%20you%20don't%20disable%20them%20and%20forget%20to%20plug%20them%20back%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20smoke%20detector%20do%20firefighters%20recommend%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20fire%20marshal%20with%20over%20two%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20fire%20service%2C%20Sayles%20chooses%20hardwired%2C%20dual-sensor%20alarms%20with%20replaceable%20batteries%20and%20interconnect%20capabilities%20to%20protect%20his%20own%20home.%20When%20purchasing%20any%20smoke%20alarm%2C%20Sayles%20says%20to%20do%20your%20due%20diligence.%20%26quot%3BPurchase%20UL-listed%20alarms%2C%20understand%20the%20features%2C%20confirm%20compatibility%20if%20alarms%20are%20interconnected%2C%20and%20follow%20manufacturer%20guidance.%20The%20'best'%20alarm%20is%20the%20one%20that%20is%20properly%20installed%2C%20maintained%2C%20and%20replaced%20on%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20lifespan%20of%20a%20smoke%20detector%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSmoke%20alarms%20should%20be%20replaced%20according%20to%20the%20manufacturer's%20recommendations%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20every%2010%20years%2C%20or%20when%20they%20stop%20working%E2%80%94whichever%20comes%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20smoke%20alarm%20is%20more%20than%2010%20years%20old%2C%20install%20new%20alarms%20and%20look%20for%20products%20that%20are%20third-party%20listed%20or%20certified.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20often%20should%20I%20test%20my%20smoke%20detectors%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recommend%20people%20test%20their%20smoke%20alarms%20twice%20per%20year%2C%20at%20minimum%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanders%20says.%20Start%20by%20pressing%20the%20test%20button%20to%20confirm%20the%20horn%20works%20and%20the%20unit%20has%20power%20%E2%80%94%20but%20smoke%20detector%20testing%20doesn't%20end%20there.%20%26quot%3BPressing%20the%20test%20button%20only%20confirms%20the%20horn%20works%20%E2%80%94%20it%20does%20not%20verify%20that%20the%20sensor%20can%20still%20detect%20smoke%2C%26quot%3B%20Sayles%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20thorough%20testing%2C%20Sayles%20recommends%20using%20aerosol%20smoke%20products%20designed%20specifically%20for%20smoke%20alarm%20testing%2C%20both%20for%20new%20installations%20and%20routine%20bi-annual%20checks.%20%26quot%3BTo%20use%20them%20correctly%2C%20homeowners%20should%20follow%20the%20manufacturer's%20instructions%2C%20spray%20the%20test%20aerosol%20near%20(not%20directly%20into)%20the%20alarm%2C%20and%20confirm%20that%20the%20alarm%20activates%20promptly.%20A%20proper%20response%20means%20the%20alarm%20sounds%20within%20seconds%20and%20resets%20normally%20afterward.%20If%20it%20does%20not%20activate%20or%20behaves%20erratically%2C%20the%20detector%20should%20be%20replaced%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-smoke-detectors%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772042030000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f12d5e8408f6671803a44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-smoke-detectors%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20best%20smoke%20detectors%20provide%20reliable%20alerts%20and%20feature%20interconnectivity%2C%20dual-sensors%2C%20and%20a%20backup%20battery%20to%20help%20protect%20your%20home.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Janelle%20Leeson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-smoke-detectors%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reliance%20Enterprise%20Intelligence%20ceases%20to%20be%20wholly%20owned%20arm%20of%20RIL%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772041901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-12%2F10%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F1200X630%2F1733795156-91.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmeta-takes-30-stake-in-reliance-enterprise-intelligence-via-share-issue-126022501292_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reliance%20Enterprise%20Intelligence%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20wholly%20owned%20step-down%20subsidiary%20of%20RIL%20after%20issuing%20shares%20to%20a%20Meta%20unit%2C%20which%20now%20holds%2030%25%20of%20its%20equity%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmeta-takes-30-stake-in-reliance-enterprise-intelligence-via-share-issue-126022501292_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmeta-takes-30-stake-in-reliance-enterprise-intelligence-via-share-issue-126022501292_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmeta-takes-30-stake-in-reliance-enterprise-intelligence-via-share-issue-126022501292_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Pentagon%20picks%20what%20drones%20to%20buy%20in%20a%20Chinese-dominated%20market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20small%20quadcopter%20drone%20flies%20in%20a%20blue%20sky%20with%20a%20trail%20of%20smoke%20behind%20it.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f2559e8408f6671803c84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Blue%20UAS%20List%20has%20a%20rigorous%20process%20for%20selecting%20drones%20that%20US%20military%20personnel%20can%20use.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Anthony%20Herrera%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Pentagon%20has%20a%20list%20of%20drones%20approved%20for%20military%20personnel%20to%20buy%20and%20use.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Blue%20UAS%20List%20is%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20DoD%20is%20dealing%20with%20China's%20dominance%20of%20the%20drone%20market%20and%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoD%20has%20a%20larger%20focus%20on%20buying%20more%20drones%20and%20boosting%20US%20drone%20production.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20is%20rapidly%20embracing%20drones%20across%20the%20services%20and%20steering%20troops%20toward%20systems%20vetted%20to%20avoid%20Chinese%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20reflects%20a%20broader%20Pentagon%20effort%20to%20field%20large%20numbers%20of%20low-cost%20drones%20quickly%20without%20creating%20new%20dependencies%20that%20could%20backfire%20in%20a%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Blue%20UAS%20%5BUncrewed%20Aerial%20Systems%5D%20List%20provides%20service%20branches%20and%20federal%20agencies%20with%20a%20catalog%20of%20approved%20drones%20they%20can%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approval%20process%20focuses%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-making-next-day-fixes-on-new-warfighting-software-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echeaper%2C%20off-the-shelf%20UAS%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20can%20easily%20buy%20and%20upgrade.%20The%20criteria%20for%20the%20list%20align%20with%20the%20Pentagon's%20wider%20drone%20strategy%2C%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-taps-companies-ukrainian-for-attack-drones-competition-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDrone%20Dominance%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20testing%20commercial%20platforms%20from%2025%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Blue%20UAS%20program%20was%20established%20in%202020%20to%20identify%20drones%20compliant%20with%20US%20government%20standards%2C%20particularly%20cybersecurity%20and%20supply-chain%20rules.%20In%20December%202025%2C%20the%20Defense%20Contract%20Management%20Agency%20launched%20an%20official%20Blue%20UAS%20List%20website%20cataloging%20the%20models%20that%20military%20personnel%20could%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DCMA%20said%20that%20the%20list%20would%20expedite%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20process%20of%20getting%20drones%20into%20troops'%20hands%2C%20help%20jump-start%20investments%20in%20UAS%20technologies%20in%20the%20drone%20industrial%20base%2C%20and%20spark%20reforms%20in%20DoD's%20acquisition%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty-four%20drones%20have%20been%20cleared%20for%20training%20use%2C%20and%2029%20have%20passed%20additional%20reviews%20for%20operational%20deployment.%20Those%20selected%20drones%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoast-guard-drone-hunt-drug-runners-landmark-cocaine-haul-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShield%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E's%20V-Bat%2C%20Skydio-made%20drones%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-racing-gave-birth-to-this-cutting-edge-drone-company-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPerformance%20Drone%20Works%3C%2Fa%3E'%20C100%2C%20and%20AeroEnvironment's%20Red%20Dragon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20works%20on%20a%20small%20drone%20on%20a%20wooden%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69989ed4156648bc16a89b07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20included%20an%20innovation%20lane%20focused%20on%20evaluating%20soldier-made%20drones.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Aaron%20Troutman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20Blue%20UAS%20List%2C%20drones%20have%20to%20meet%20strict%20legal%2C%20cybersecurity%2C%20and%20operational%20requirements.%20Assessments%20are%20completed%20on%20whether%20the%20drones%20have%20any%20vulnerabilities%2C%20such%20as%20parts%20sourced%20from%20certain%20foreign%20countries%20or%20exposure%20to%20supply%20chain%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20range%20of%20drones%2C%20drone%20parts%2C%20and%20software%20are%20part%20of%20the%20Blue%20UAS%20program.%20Many%20of%20the%20approved%20systems%20are%20tailored%20to%20specific%20missions%20but%20can%20be%20modified%20or%20upgraded%20as%20requirements%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20factors%20in%20creating%20this%20list%20was%20concerns%20over%20a%20Chinese-dominated%20drone%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Association%20for%20Uncrewed%20Vehicle%20Systems%20International%2C%20Chinese%20companies%20control%2090%25%20of%20the%20commercial%20drone%20market.%20US%20officials%20have%20said%20the%20Blue%20UAS%20List%20is%20an%20effort%20to%20curb%20China's%20leverage%20over%20the%20market%2C%20including%20over%20key%20components%20such%20as%20motors%20that%20Beijing%20could%20restrict%20in%20a%20conflict%2C%20potentially%20disrupting%20US%20drone%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20Blue%20UAS%20List's%20goal%20of%20compiling%20drones%20that%20aren't%20reliant%20on%20Chinese%20parts%2C%20sources%20told%20DefenseScoop%20last%20November%20that%20most%20of%20the%20approved%20drones%20rely%20on%20Chinese-made%20motors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20these%20Chinese-made%20motors%20are%20referred%20to%20as%20'dumb%20components'%20experts%20say%20the%20issue%20is%20less%20about%20espionage%20risk%20and%20more%20about%20availability%20and%20resilience%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20Institute%20for%20Defense%20and%20Government%20Advancement%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20conflict%20or%20trade%20disruption%2C%20US%20drone%20production%20could%20stall%20almost%20immediately%20due%20to%20reliance%20on%20Chinese%20supply%20chains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican-made%20motors%20are%20typically%20more%20expensive%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20how%20quickly%20Washington%20can%20scale%20domestic%20production%20and%20drive%20down%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226348%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sits%20with%20a%20VR%20headset%20on%20and%20holds%20a%20drone%20controller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6983afa8d3c7faef0ecda11b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224232%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20drone%20program%20is%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20DoD%20is%20expediting%20the%20development%20and%20implementation%20of%20small%20drones%20across%20forces.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%20photo%20by%20Cpl.%20Joshua%20Bustamante%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaiwan-needs-tech-industries-involved-in-drone-push-us-official-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChina-free%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20defense%20supply%20chain%20are%20more%20broadly%20sparking%20investments%20in%20a%20stronger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-borrowing-from-ukraines-diy-drone-warfare-strategy-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmerican-made%20drone%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20an%20aspect%20of%20the%20Pentagon's%20Drone%20Dominance%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20US%20Secretary%20of%20Defense%20Pete%20Hegseth%20announced%20the%20Pentagon's%20drone%20priorities%20in%20July%202025%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20DoD%20would%20bolster%20US%20drone%20manufacturing%2C%20support%20investments%20in%20the%20domestic%20industry%2C%20and%20push%20for%20more%20low-cost%20drones%20and%20technological%20evolutions%20to%20get%20more%20drones%20to%20troops%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoD%20ultimately%20aims%20to%20field%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20low-cost%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-drone-school-training-students-what-like-be-hunted-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone-way%20attack%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%202027.%20It%20has%20said%20it%20will%20invest%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20in%20the%20drone%20market%20over%20the%20next%20two%20years%20through%20the%20Drone%20Dominance%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20development%20in%20the%20Drone%20Dominance%20Program%20is%20an%20initial%20test%20on%20one-way%20attack%20drones%2C%20which%20is%20happening%20now%20through%20next%20month%20at%20Fort%20Benning%20in%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20testing%2C%20called%20Gauntlet%2C%20involves%20drones%20from%20over%20two%20dozen%20companies%2C%20including%20a%20lot%20of%20smaller%20startups%20and%20two%20Ukrainian%20firms.%20When%20Gauntlet's%20done%2C%20DoD%20will%20buy%20roughly%20%24150%20million%20in%20prototypes%20of%20selected%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20Gauntlet%20is%20not%20itself%20a%20formal%20Blue%20UAS%20listing%20action%2C%20it%20is%20tightly%20aligned%20with%20the%20program's%20purpose%20and%20trajectory%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20IDGA%20report%20said.%20It%20reflects%20DoD's%20shift%20toward%20iterative%2C%20competitive%20acquisition%20of%20new%20weapons%20that%20occur%20in%20months%20rather%20than%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-drones-chinese-dominated-market-list-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772041859000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f273d50f42603b0f8e130%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-drones-chinese-dominated-market-list-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Blue%20UAS%20List%20vets%20commercial%20drones%20for%20security%20and%20supply%20chain%20risks.%20The%20program%20is%20one%20part%20of%20DoD's%20bet%20on%20drone%20warfare.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-drones-chinese-dominated-market-list-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anil%20Ambani's%20house%20worth%20%E2%82%B93.7K%20crore%20attached%20by%20ED%20under%20PMLA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772039710000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2025-08%2F08%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F1200X630%2F1754676289-8785.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fed-attaches-reliance-group-chairman-anil-ambani-s-abode-worth-3-716-cr-126022500929_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20attached%20Reliance%20Group%20chairman%20Anil%20Ambani's%20Mumbai%20house%2C%20'Abode'%2C%20worth%20Rs%203%2C716%20crore%20under%20the%20anti-money%20laundering%20law%2C%20official%20sources%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C